# Day 7 – Testing & Salesforce DX

## 1. Why Testing Matters

Testing is important in Salesforce because enterprise applications handle critical business data such as customers, sales, payments, and support operations. A small bug can affect thousands of users and records.

Testing helps developers:

- Verify that Apex code works correctly
- Prevent future bugs during deployments
- Ensure business logic behaves as expected
- Improve software quality and reliability
- Validate automation processes
- Meet Salesforce deployment requirements

In Salesforce, at least 75% Apex code coverage is required before deploying code to production.

Testing also helps teams confidently release updates without breaking existing features.

