# 6. Reflection

Enterprise software development requires structured workflows because large organizations manage huge amounts of business-critical data and processes.

Without proper workflows:
- Bugs increase
- Deployments fail
- Teams lose coordination
- Data becomes inconsistent

Structured workflows provide:
- Better collaboration
- Reliable deployments
- Higher software quality
- Easier maintenance
- Strong security and governance

Salesforce development combines testing, automation, version control, and deployment practices to build scalable enterprise applications efficiently.
